The preference pane bundle normally contains a nib file with the user interface for modifying user preferences. The nib file contains a window assigned to the _window outlet of the preference pane instance (the nib’s File’s Owner). The

, invoked by the preference application, loads the nib file and uses the content view of _window as the preference pane’s main view. Override this method if you need a different technique for creating the user interface.
subclass is responsible for initializing the user interface with the current preference settings and recording any modifications the user makes. Through a series of

methods, the preference application notifies the preference pane when the pane is selected (displayed) and deselected, allowing the pane to perform the necessary actions at the appropriate times. Implement these methods (and any additional target-action methods connected to the interface) as needed to produce the desired behavior for your preference pane.
